<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-09T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="765" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 872.48/175</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Special Agent in Corfu</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DHP2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dodge</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-09T17:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your June 24, 4 p.m. American Red Cross has purchased all supplies for
                            Serbian prisoners under direction of Serbian Minister. At one time it
                            had purchased supplies considerably in excess of money which Serbian
                            Minister had placed in its hands. At present time has no money on
                            deposit for account of Serbian Government. Serbian Minister has
                            requested his Government for authorization to place additional money to
                            credit of Red Cross for purchase additional supplies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>